Dakshinayana, a group of various progressive organisations, will organise a one-day national-level conference on Peace, harmony and tolerance in Gujarat on Saturday to commemorate the assassination of Mahatma Gandhi.District unit president of Prajna Kanoonu Salaha Samiti K. Neela addressing presspersons here on Wednesday said that around 100 people, including 25 from Kalaburagi district, from various organisations in the State will participate in the conference.G.N. Devy, literary critic, who returned his Padma Srhi award in protest against the killing of scholar M.M. Kalburgi, will speak on the issue of intolerance. .